        <div class="frontpage-initiative-announcements grid-1-3">
         <article class="wu-card">
          <header class="wu-card-header">
           <h3 class="wu-card-title">
            <a class="link-heading" href="https://diversity.wustl.edu/university-creates-center-for-the-study-of-race-ethnicity-equity/">
             University creates Center for the Study of Race, Ethnicity &amp; Equity
            </a>
           </h3>
           <div class="wu-card-meta">
            Mar 06
           </div>
          </header>
          <div class="wu-card-content">
           <p class="wu-card-excerpt">
            Chancellor-elect Andrew D. Martin announced the creation of a university wide Center for the Study of Race, Ethnicity &amp; Equity. “The Center… will promote path-breaking research that deepens knowledge and shapes national dialogue; facilitate student learning; and provide an infrastructure for our faculty members to engage in public discourse and policy design both locally and regionally.” Click here to read more about the new Center being led by Vice Provost Adrienne Davis.
           </p>
          </div>
         </article>
         <article class="wu-card">
          <figure class="wu-card-figure-thumbnail">
