     <section class="frontpage-training band bg-purple">
      <div class="container">
       <h2 class="section-heading">
        Increasing Understanding
       </h2>
       <p class="section-intro">
        In order to prepare our students to live and work in an increasingly diverse world, the WashU community is learning together through a robust training program of workshops and dialogues designed to improve the campus culture and climate.
       </p>
       <div class="grid">
        <div class="frontpage-training-promos grid-1-2 text-centered">
         <div class="grid">
          <div class="wu-tout grid-1-2">
           <div class="wu-display-number">
            49
           </div>
           <p>
            Departments and groups trained by SafeZones to promote more secure environments for LBGTQIA* students.
           </p>
          </div>
          <div class="wu-tout grid-1-2">
           <div class="wu-display-number">
            60
            <span class="wu-display-number-unit">
             %
            </span>
           </div>
           <p>
            School of Medicine departments that have completed all diversity and inclusion training sessions.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
         <a class="button-inverse" href="/training">
          Learn about diversity training opportunities
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="frontpage-training-profile grid-1-2">
         <div class="wu-profile wu-profile-split-rev bg-purple-light">
          <figure class="wu-profile-image-wrap">
           <img alt="" class="wu-profile-image" height="660" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="https://diversity.wustl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/profile-mackenziehineswilson.jpg" srcset="https://diversity.wustl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/profile-mackenziehineswilson.jpg 600w, https://diversity.wustl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/profile-mackenziehineswilson-273x300.jpg 273w, https://diversity.wustl.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/profile-mackenziehineswilson-400x440.jpg 400w" width="600">
